    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                
            <pb facs="liv_002285_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName>8 Dover Street</placeName>
<lb/><placeName>Piccadilly</placeName> 
<lb/><date when="1865-05-04">4<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May 1865</date></dateline>
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Hamilton</persName></salute></opener>
<lb/><p>Will you kindly
<lb/>forward <bibl>this note</bibl>
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Brodie</persName>?</p>
<lb/><p>A gentleman
<lb/>called <persName>Robert
<lb/>Arthington</persName> of
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="city">Leeds</settlement></placeName> wishes to
<lb/>make an effort
<lb/>to introduce the
<lb/><bibl>bible</bibl> into <placeName><country>Angola</country></placeName></p>

<lb/><cb/><ab>not knowing <choice><sic><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Brodie</persName>s</sic><corr><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Brodie</persName>'s</corr></choice> address
<lb/>I venture to trouble you</ab> <closer><salute>With kind
<lb/>regards to
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> <choice><abbr>H</abbr><expan>Hamilton</expan></choice></persName> &amp;
<lb/>family</salute>
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>
            </div>
            
            <div>
                 <pb facs="liv_002285_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">He has been led to
<lb/>this from reading
<lb/>my account of
<lb/>that country - He <!-- geog:  -->
<lb/>seems of a very
<lb/>ardent temperament
<lb/>uses the word
<lb/>Hallelujah! in <bibl>his
<lb/>letters</bibl> and is
<lb/>possessed of
<lb/>means - I <choice><sic>dont</sic><corr>don't</corr></choice>
<lb/>know him at
<lb/>all more that he
<lb/>sometimes writes
<lb/>to me, and in the 
<lb/>course he proposed
<lb/>to adopt I feared</p>

<lb/><cb/><ab><persName>Sir Roderick</persName> had a thousand at
<lb/>his reception last night</ab>

                 <pb facs="liv_002285_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">that he might lose a
<lb/>deal of money &amp; do
<lb/>no good. I therefore
<lb/>advised caution
<lb/>in dealing with the
<lb/><term type="people">Portuguese</term>. This
<lb/>advice he has
<lb/>taken in good spirit
<lb/>and now asks me
<lb/>to tell him what
<lb/>salary outfit
<lb/>passage money &amp;c
<lb/>ought to be given
<lb/>to a man who
<lb/>has been <supplied cert="high">an</supplied> <term type="occupation">agent</term> for
<lb/><orgName><term type="nationality">British</term> &amp; <choice><abbr>F.</abbr><expan cert="high"><term type="nationality">Foreign</term></expan></choice> Bible <!-- Adrian, it's not letting me use bibl tag for Bible here...any suggestions? HB --><!-- I don't see a way to fix this other than removing the <orgName> tag, so we have to choose one or the other. I've left as is, but added a comment for bibl. AW --><!-- bibl: Bible -->
<lb/>Society</orgName> who <w>propo<supplied cert="high">se</supplied></w>
<lb/>to settle at <placeName><settlement type="town">Loanda</settlement></placeName></p>

<lb/><cb/><ab>Everybody was there &amp; <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Beke</persName>
<lb/><unclear cert="low">He</unclear> would be source of the <placeName><geogName type="river">Nile</geogName></placeName> man</ab>
<!-- alternatively, there might be a metamark just before the ampersand intended to bring in part or all of the 2nd line. So it would then read "Everybody was there who would be source of the Nile man & Dr Beke" AM --><!-- Doesn't look like it to me. Let's leave as is. AW -->

                 <pb facs="liv_002285_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><p>I advise him now
<lb/>to apply to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Silva</persName>
<lb/>through your elder
<lb/>and tell him that
<lb/>I <choice><sic>dont</sic><corr>don't</corr></choice> know <w>any<supplied>-</supplied>
<lb break="no"/>thing</w> of <choice><sic><persName>Silva</persName>s</sic><corr><persName>Silva</persName>'s</corr></choice> religious
<lb/>feelings but that
<lb/>the <term type="people">Portuguese</term>
<lb/>generally have very
<lb/>weak religious
<lb/>convictions and
<lb/>I have given him
<lb/><choice><sic><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Brodie</persName>s</sic><corr><persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Brodie</persName>'s</corr></choice> card
<lb/>with the assurance
<lb/>that he will have
<lb/><term type="faith">Christian</term> sympathy
<lb/>with him. The
<lb/>card is gone and <!-- I think this continues onto the vertical text on p1 AM --><!-- Seems likely and is a typical Livingstone practice. AW -->
</p>
            </div>
